intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Implement a standard information retrieval (IR) system;
Discuss the theoretical basis behind the standard models of IR (e.g. Boolean, Vector-space, and Probabilistic models);
Discuss how an IR system should be evaluated in terms of the system’s performance and the user’s satisfaction with the system;
Describe the techniques in organising information;
Describe the techniques involved in retrieving information from the World Wide Web;
Describe the practical engineering issues raised by the implementation of a search engine for the Web.
